ce:section.ce:para:
For detecting the active species during photocatalytic reactivity, hydroxyl radicals (
                        OH), superoxide radicals (O2



                           −
                        ), holes (h+
                        ) and electrons (e−
                        ) were investigated by adding 1.0mM IPA (a quencher of 
                        OH) [50,51], 1mM p-benzoquinone (BQ, a quencher of O2



                           −
                        )[36,50], 1mM KI (a quencher of h+
                        )[15] and 1mM tertiary butanol (TBA) for e−
                        , respectively. The method was similar to the former photocatalytic activity test.
